.TH "gfs2_adjust_quota" 9 "gfs2_adjust_quota" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_adjust_quota \- adjust record of current block usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_adjust_quota
.BI "(struct gfs2_inode *ip "  ","
.BI "loff_t loc "  ","
.BI "s64 change "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_quota_data *qd "  ","
.BI "struct qc_dqblk *fdq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
The quota inode
.IP "loc" 12
Offset of the entry in the quota file
.IP "change" 12
The amount of usage change to record
.IP "qd" 12
The quota data
.IP "fdq" 12
The updated limits to record
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function was mostly borrowed from gfs2_block_truncate_page which was
in turn mostly borrowed from ext3
.SH "RETURN"
0 or -ve on error
